<TITLE> Indian inflation seen coming under control: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 New Delhi, Sep 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Inflation seems to be coming under control and upcoming harvests are expected to be good, the chief of the prime minister's economic advisory council said on Friday, which could help price pressures ease further. "Coming harvest seems to be reasonably comfortable and ... the inflation situation may be coming under control," Suresh Tendulkar said at a seminar in the Indian capital. Data released on Thursday showed inflation edged up in early September to 12.14 percent after easing for three straight weeks
